Development enviroment settup (Windows-Android)
1. Install Chocolatey: [Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol = [Net.SecurityProtocolType]::Tls12; iex ((new-object net.webclient).DownloadString('https://chocolatey.org/install.ps1')) 
//notice1: use "[Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol = [Net.SecurityProtocolType]::Tls12; ” to avoid tls version mismatch error, most windows user has this error.
//notice2: error "because running scripts is disabled on this system." --> sol: Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned, change the executionPolicy from Restricted to RemoteSigned, there are four execution policies for PowerShell: Restricted, AllSigned, RemoteSigned, Unrestricted
2. install nodejs (you could use chocolatey to install or install from the official website directly)
2.1 chocolatey: choco install nodejs.install
2.2 website: https://nodejs.org/en/download/
2.3 after installing node.js, npm is also installed simultaneously, which is a package management provided by node.js.
You can also download yarn, which is privided by facebook, to accelarate module downloading for node.js.
yarn add == npm install --save
3. Install Android Studio: It's just an IDE, you can also use other IDEs like VS code, Sublime or Atom.
If you are not using Android Studio, then you will need to install Android SDK.





